Which of the following is used as a system- wide cron file?
A)  /etc/cron.d
B)  /etc/cron.sys
C)  /etc/crontab
D)  /etc/cron.tab
C
C. The /etc/crontab file is a plain- text file that is treated as a system- wide cron file. Assuch, the file is generally not associated with any single user, and its not necessary to run aspecial command after editing this file.
